<blockquote>
  <p>From Patrick Coate, a new and improved version of the game rock-paper-scissors:</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <p>Besides the usual three options that players have ‚Äî rock, paper or scissors ‚Äî let‚Äôs add a fourth option, double scissors, which is played by making a scissors with two fingers on each side (like a Vulcan salute). Double scissors, being larger and tougher, defeat regular scissors, and just like regular scissors, they cut paper and are smashed by rock. The three traditional options interact just as they do in the standard game.</p>
